), and Thailand (
<bibRefCitation author="Wongsiri, N" journalOrPublisher="Tijdschrift voor Entomologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" refId="B61" refString="Wongsiri, N, 1991. List of Insect, Mite and Other Zoological Pests of Economic Plants in Thailand. Entomology and Zoology Division, Department of Agriculture, Bangkok." title="List of Insect, Mite and Other Zoological Pests of Economic Plants in Thailand. Entomology and Zoology Division, Department of Agriculture, Bangkok." year="1991">Wongsiri 1991</bibRefCitation>
) are most likely to refer to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. subcostata" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="subcostata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">B. subcostata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The type of 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. occipitale" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="occipitale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">N. occipitale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jacoby (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Basilepta viridipennis (Jacoby). a, b. Syntype of Nodostoma occipitale Jacoby, a synonym of B. viridipennis (BMNH); c, d. Colour forms of B. viridipennis." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.47447.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/364595" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" tableDoi="10.3897/dez.66.47447.figure9">Fig. 9a, b</figureCitation>
) (BMNH, examined), a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. viridipennis" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="viridipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">B. viridipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, has only a superficial resemblance to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. subcostata" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="subcostata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">B. subcostata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be easily separated from the latter by the pronotum forming an obtuse angle posterolaterally (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Basilepta viridipennis (Jacoby). a, b. Syntype of Nodostoma occipitale Jacoby, a synonym of B. viridipennis (BMNH); c, d. Colour forms of B. viridipennis." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.66.47447.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/364595" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" tableDoi="10.3897/dez.66.47447.figure9">Fig. 9b</figureCitation>
) and its lateral margins abruptly converging anteriorly in almost a straight line. Besides, pronotal punctures in 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. viridipennis" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="viridipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">B. viridipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are smaller than average elytral punctures and finely and more closely impressed on lateral part and more sparsely and finely so on median and anterior parts. 
<taxonomicName authority="Baly, 1860" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Basilepta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Basilepta viridipennis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridipennis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">Basilepta viridipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is of variable coloration and includes reddish, brownish, bluish, greenish, violaceous, and blackish forms. 
<bibRefCitation author="Medvedev, LN" journalOrPublisher="Russian Entomological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" pagination="409 - 417" publicationUrl="http://zmmu.msu.ru/files/images/spec/Russ%20Ent%20J/REJ_15-4_409-417%20%28Medvedev%29.pdf" refId="B39" refString="Medvedev, LN, 2006. To the knowledge of Chrysomelidae (Coleoptera) described by V. Motschulsky. Russian Entomological Journal 15: 409 - 417" title="To the knowledge of Chrysomelidae (Coleoptera) described by V. Motschulsky." url="http://zmmu.msu.ru/files/images/spec/Russ%20Ent%20J/REJ_15-4_409-417%20%28Medvedev%29.pdf" volume="15" year="2006">Medvedev (2006)</bibRefCitation>
designated a lectotype for 
<taxonomicName genus="N." lsidName="N. viridipenne" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" rank="species" species="viridipenne">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">N. viridipenne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and synonymised 
<taxonomicName authority="Baly, 1860" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Basilepta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Basilepta frontalis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="179" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="frontalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="179">Basilepta frontalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Baly) with it, as he found the types of both species were identical.
</paragraph>
